HEADWORD: Whacker
<hw>Whack"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>One who whacks.</def> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Anything very large; specif., a great lie; a
whopper.</def> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark> <rj><au>Halliwell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

